HEADWORD: Dagan
<hw>Dagan</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>the Mesopotanian god of
agriculture and earth; it is a counterpart of Phoenician and Philistine
Dagon.</def> <note>See references to Dagon in the Bible and in the opera
<title>Samson et Dalila</title>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

